```java
@GetResource(path = "/changeRecord/page", requiredPermission = false)
@Operation(summary = "查询空间站变更记录（产品后台）")
public ResponseData<PageInfo<SpaceChangeRecordVo>> changeRecordPage(SpaceChangeRecordPageRo ro) {
    Long userId = SessionContext.getUserId();
    UserSimpleInfoVo userSimpleInfoVo = apitableGrpcClientService.getUserById(userId);
    if (userSimpleInfoVo == null || !allowUserList.contains(userSimpleInfoVo.getNickName())) {
        throw new BusinessException("No Authorization");
    }
    PageInfo<SpaceChangeRecordVo> result = spaceChangeRecordQueryManager.page(
            ro.getSpaceId(), ro.getType(), ro.getPageNum(), ro.getPageSize());
    return ResponseData.success(result);
}
```

## Context

- `SpaceChangeRecordQueryManager` was created in the previous task, with a `page(spaceId, type, pageNum, pageSize)` method
- `SpaceChangeRecordPageRo` extends `BasePageRo` (has `pageNum`, `pageSize`) and adds `spaceId`, `type`
- The super-admin verification pattern (checking `allowUserList` with nickname) is copied from `SpaceController.verifyAuth()`
- `SpaceHolder.get()` retrieves the spaceId from the request header in the cockpit context
- `requiredSpaceAdmin = true` means only the main space admin can access (cockpit entry)
- `requiredPermission = false` with manual super-admin check is used for the management backend entry

